abstract: House votes 241 to 179 to cut funds for so-called sanctuary cities, jurisdictions shielding illegal immigrants from federal immigration officials; vote corresponds with Republican crackdown after authorities in San Francisco released illegal immigrant with criminal record who subsequently killed a woman there.
lead_paragraph: Republicans led the move in response to the killing of a young woman by an illegal immigrant in San Francisco.

headline.main: House Votes to Cut Funds for ‘Sanctuary Cities’
